Suzanne Cleminshaw is an American writer based in Britain. Her book, The Great Ideas, was shortlisted for the First Novel category at the 1999 Whitbread Awards.[1] She studied creative writing at the University of East Anglia.[2] She is Buzz Aldrin's niece.[1] 
